{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784198692257,"sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_45c0a51cd18f46e99b2091e5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":88,"limit":45},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n88: ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n89: - Completed pivots: 0\n90: - Failed pivots: 0\n91: - Audited overrides: 0\n92: - Saturated: none yet\n93: - Pivot lineage: none yet (convergence mode off; telemetry only)\n94: - Remaining frontier: broadening angles into auth depth, gating, and transport-packet conventions\n95: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n100: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n101: [Populated after iteration 1 completes]\n102: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n107: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n108: Iteration 1: Broad survey — fetch https://refero.design/mcp and the `refero_skill` repo README/structure to inventory the tool surface, search workflow vocabulary (apps/screens/flows/elements), and capture the documented MCP endpoint/auth story; cross-reference the existing `.utcp_config.json` `refero` manual.\n109: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n114: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n115: \n116: ### Bounded Context Snapshot (from packet docs + repo artifacts)\n117: \n118: - **Pinned sources**: `context/website-link.md` → `https://refero.design/mcp` (product/MCP page) and `https://github.com/referodesign/refero_skill` (official skill repo).\n119: - **Existing transport**: `.utcp_config.json` manual `refero` — `call_template_type: mcp`, transport `stdio`, command `npx -y mcp-remote https://api.refero.design/mcp`, empty `env`. This is the live Code Mode transport under test; read-only reference (not modified in this phase).\n120: - **Sibling pattern**: `.opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/mcp-figma/` — an existing MCP transport mode (CLI-primary + optional Code Mode MCP). Establishes the transport-packet convention: SKILL.md + references (tool_surface, mcp_wiring, troubleshooting) + assets (utcp manual, env template). `mcp-refero` will be read-only/Code-Mode-only (no CLI primary), a simpler shape than mcp-figma.\n121: - **Hub router**: `.opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/` is a parent hub; `mcp-refero` will register in `mode-registry.json` (phase 003, not this phase).\n122: - **Phase map**: 001-research → 002-skill-authoring → 003-hub-integration → 004-validation-and-handoff. This lineage feeds 002.\n123: - resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.\n124: \n125: ### Source of truth\n126: Research is read-only discovery over web sources + the repo's `.utcp_config.json` manual. Live-surface claims not directly probed must be marked inferred.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n131: \n132: - Max iterations: 2 (`stopPolicy: max-iterations`; convergence telemetry-only)\n\n(Showing lines 88-132 of 141. Use offset=133 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet (convergence mode off; telemetry only)\n- Remaining frontier: broadening angles into auth depth, gating, and transport-packet conventions\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n[Populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet (convergence mode off; telemetry only)\n- Remaining frontier: broadening angles into auth depth, gating, and transport-packet conventions\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n[Populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\nIteration 1: Broad survey — fetch https://refero.design/mcp and the `refero_skill` repo README/structure to inventory the tool surface, search workflow vocabulary (apps/screens/flows/elements), and capture the documented MCP endpoint/auth story; cross-reference the existing `.utcp_config.json` `refero` manual.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot (from packet docs + repo artifacts)\n\n- **Pinned sources**: `context/website-link.md` → `https://refero.design/mcp` (product/MCP page) and `https://github.com/referodesign/refero_skill` (official skill repo).\n- **Existing transport**: `.utcp_config.json` manual `refero` — `call_template_type: mcp`, transport `stdio`, command `npx -y mcp-remote https://api.refero.design/mcp`, empty `env`. This is the live Code Mode transport under test; read-only reference (not modified in this phase).\n- **Sibling pattern**: `.opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/mcp-figma/` — an existing MCP transport mode (CLI-primary + optional Code Mode MCP). Establishes the transport-packet convention: SKILL.md + references (tool_surface, mcp_wiring, troubleshooting) + assets (utcp manual, env template). `mcp-refero` will be read-only/Code-Mode-only (no CLI primary), a simpler shape than mcp-figma.\n- **Hub router**: `.opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/` is a parent hub; `mcp-refero` will register in `mode-registry.json` (phase 003, not this phase).\n- **Phase map**: 001-research → 002-skill-authoring → 003-hub-integration → 004-validation-and-handoff. This lineage feeds 002.\n- resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.\n\n### Source of truth\nResearch is read-only discovery over web sources + the repo's `.utcp_config.json` manual. Live-surface claims not directly probed must be marked inferred.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 2 (`stopPolicy: max-iterations`; convergence telemetry-only)","lineStart":88,"lineEnd":132,"totalLines":141,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784198692251,"end":1784198692256}},"id":"prt_f6a877d98001TTzAftnBeyYFb6","sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","messageID":"msg_f6a87550b001xkw5uK2hm0mX13"}}
