ure the documented MCP endpoint/auth story; cross-reference the existing `.utcp_config.json` `refero` manual.\n+Iteration 2 (broaden angles — convergence is telemetry-only): (a) free-vs-paid gating + rate limits via `refero.design` root/pricing or README signals; (b) auth/token lifecycle depth for mcp-remote and how the transport packet documents first-use interactive sign-in vs. a Bearer token; (c) explicit `mcp-refero` transport-packet file layout mapped onto the mcp-figma convention (tool_surface taxonomy, mcp_wiring, troubleshooting, env_template) so phase 002 can author without re-discovery.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n \n ---\n \n","additions":1,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784198740765,"end":1784198740767}},"id":"prt_f6a883b00001x09t8jG7mb23k1","sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","messageID":"msg_f6a87b9a0001i3bu1sbqr6mxRu"}}
