{"type":"text","timestamp":1784198781888,"sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","part":{"id":"prt_f6a88dba4001s6fAFU47ockL0R","messageID":"msg_f6a88440e001IUyO97OcQMBZ0n","sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","type":"text","text":"Updating findings registry and generating the dashboard after iteration 1.","time":{"start":1784198781860,"end":1784198781881}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784198781888,"sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_a3a082c667714c52900ded0a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Deep Research Dashboard — lineage:glm\n\nAuto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state. Overwritten each iteration.\n\n## Iteration Table\n\n| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |\n|-----|-------|--------------|----------------|--------|\n| 1 | Broad survey: tool surface (8 tools), auth model, coverage limits, skill-vs-transport conventions | 1.0 | 6 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n**3 / 6 answered**\n\n- ✅ Q1 — Tool surface (8 tools, 3 layers) — iteration 1\n- ✅ Q5 — Skill-repo conventions (MIT; SKILL.md + references/ + assets/) — iteration 1\n- ✅ Q6 — Transport-packet design (read-only Code-Mode-only peer of mcp-figma) — iteration 1\n- ⬜ Q2 — Auth/token lifecycle detail (open: first-use interactive sign-in vs Bearer token)\n- ⬜ Q3 — Rate limits (open: undocumented in skill repo)\n- ⬜ Q4 — Free vs paid gating (open: tier boundaries undocumented)\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n- Ratios: 1.0\n- Direction: n/a (single data point)\n- **Note:** `stopPolicy = max-iterations` (cap 2). Convergence signals are **telemetry-only** this run; the loop broadens review angles rather than synthesizing early.\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- Scraping `refero.design/mcp` SPA body (yields title only).\n\n## Blocked Stops\n\nNone. (Hard max-iteration stop is terminal; no legal-stop gate evaluation needed.)\n\n## Graph Convergence\n\nNo `graphEvents` emitted this run.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nIteration 2 — broaden into free-vs-paid gating, rate limits, auth/token lifecycle, and the explicit mcp-refero transport-packet file layout mapped onto the mcp-figma convention.\n\n## Active Risks\n\n- `refero.design/mcp` SPA is unscrapable; pricing/gating/rate-limit facts may be partially inferred (iteration 2 will attempt alternate URLs).\n- Rate limits appear entirely undocumented in the official skill repo.\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-dashboard.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-dashboard.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1784198781879,"end":1784198781884}},"id":"prt_f6a88dba8001ZyfTU8hHEy0Sfb","sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","messageID":"msg_f6a88440e001IUyO97OcQMBZ0n"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784198781888,"sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_d903aae9b58347b0ab1ea5b6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"{\n  \"lineage\": \"glm\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-glm-1784198125985-iw9229\",\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research\",\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    { \"id\": \"q2\", \"text\": \"What auth model does the Refero MCP expect through mcp-remote (anonymous, OAuth, API key)?\", \"status\": \"open\", \"note\": \"Bearer-token HTTP and mcp-remote OAuth both documented at high level; token-lifecycle/first-use detail needed\" },\n    { \"id\": \"q3\", \"text\": \"What rate limits apply, and do they differ between free and paid tiers?\", \"status\": \"open\", \"note\": \"Not documented in the skill repo at all\" },\n    { \"id\": \"q4\", \"text\": \"What is the free vs paid gating — which tools/capabilities/result volumes are free vs paid-only?\", \"status\": \"open\", \"note\": \"'No account required' covers craft knowledge only; live-MCP tier boundaries undocumented\" }\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    { \"id\": \"q1\", \"text\": \"What tools does the Refero MCP server expose (names, parameters, response shapes) for UI-design-reference search across apps, screens, flows, elements?\", \"status\": \"resolved\", \"resolvedInIteration\": 1, \"evidence\": \"iteration-001.md F1\" },\n    { \"id\": \"q5\", \"text\": \"What conventions does the refero_skill repo document that the mcp-refero transport packet should mirror?\", \"status\": \"resolved\", \"resolvedInIteration\": 1, \"evidence\": \"iteration-001.md F5\" },\n    { \"id\": \"q6\", \"text\": \"How should a read-only Code-Mode-only transport packet be authored atop the existing mcp-remote manual, paired with sk-design judgment?\", \"status\": \"resolved\", \"resolvedInIteration\": 1, \"evidence\": \"iteration-001.md F5, F6\" }\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    { \"id\": \"f1\", \"iteration\": 1, \"text\": \"8 read-only tools across 3 layers: styles (search_styles, get_style), screens (search_screens, get_screen, get_similar_screens, get_screen_image), flows (search_flows, get_flow)\", \"source\": \"references/mcp-tools.md\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f2\", \"iteration\": 1, \"text\": \"Documented client mistakes: no old _tool names, no get_design_guidance, no image_size/include_similar on get_screen, no limit/image_size/include_similar on search tools, response_format only where schema shows it\", \"source\": \"references/mcp-tools.md\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f3\", \"iteration\": 1, \"text\": \"Auth: Bearer-token HTTP transport OR mcp-remote OAuth browser flow; endpoint https://api.refero.design/mcp; existing manual uses mcp-remote with empty env\", \"source\": \"README + .utcp_config.json\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f4\", \"iteration\": 1, \"text\": \"Coverage limit: styles are web-marketing-scoped only (no dashboards/auth/settings/iOS as style systems); screens+flows support platform web|ios\", \"source\": \"references/mcp-tools.md + SKILL.md\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f5\", \"iteration\": 1, \"text\": \"refero_skill is a standalone design-methodology skill (peer of sk-design), NOT an mcp-tooling transport; MIT; SKILL.md + references/ + assets/\", \"source\": \"README + SKILL.md\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f6\", \"iteration\": 1, \"text\": \"Existing .utcp_config.json manual is a minimal stdio-over-mcp-remote bridge, empty env; transport packet authored atop it read-only\", \"source\": \".utcp_config.json\" }\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    { \"approach\": \"Scrape the JS-rendered body of refero.design/mcp for structured pricing/gating data\", \"reason\": \"SPA returns only a title via WebFetch; no crawlable body\", \"evidence\": \"iteration-001.md\", \"iteration\": 1 }\n  ],\n  \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n  \"rejectedPatternIndex\": [],\n  \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n  \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": []\n}\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/findings-registry.json"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/findings-registry.json","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1784198781863,"end":1784198781886}},"id":"prt_f6a88dba50015Ln9Xjv8HlbyQ7","sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","messageID":"msg_f6a88440e001IUyO97OcQMBZ0n"}}
