{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784198815988,"sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_64e091b077fe480cab95d7fb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md","limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Figma MCP Wiring (optional, via Code Mode)\"\n3: description: \"Wiring the OPTIONAL Figma MCP into this project's Code Mode: the already-registered Framelink figma manual, the prefixed .env token, the discover-first flow, and a runnable call_tool_chain example. The CLI works fully alone; the MCP is opt-in.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"figma mcp\"\n6:   - \"figma mcp code mode\"\n7:   - \"figma-developer-mcp\"\n8:   - \"pull figma design context\"\n9:   - \"figma get_design_context\"\n10: importance_tier: \"normal\"\n11: contextType: \"implementation\"\n12: version: 1.0.0.3\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Figma MCP Wiring (optional, via Code Mode)\n16: \n17: > **IMPORTANT:** This skill works **fully with the `figma-ds-cli` alone**, and the MCP is **opt-in**. Before invoking any Figma MCP tool, always **discover first** (`search_tools` / `tool_info`) and confirm the `figma` manual and its exact tool names are present. Never guess a tool name, and never claim the MCP works until discovery confirms it.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Core Principle\n24: \n25: Wiring here means the agent reaches Figma's **read** surface (design context, variables, metadata) through this project's **Code Mode** transport. The Code Mode manual named `figma` is **already registered** in `.utcp_config.json` (community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp`, stdio, `npx`), so nothing new needs to be installed for the MCP path. The only setup step is a `.env` entry with a Figma personal access token.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: - Pull Figma file/node data into the agent so it can generate or reconcile code against a design.\n30: - The work is codegen-from-design, not authoring or exporting from the live Desktop session.\n31: \n32: The CLI vs MCP routing line:\n33: \n34: - **`figma-ds-cli` (CLI) = author/modify/export IN Figma.** It drives the live Figma Desktop session to create/render/modify nodes, manage tokens and variables, and export assets/JSX/CSS/screenshots. This is the primary surface.\n35: - **Figma MCP (Code Mode) = pull design data INTO the agent for codegen.** Use it only when the agent needs Figma design context as model input (file/node data, variables, screenshots) to generate or align code. The MCP does not drive Figma Desktop.\n36: \n37: ### Key Sources\n38: \n39: - [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - the primary CLI surface (binary identity, connect modes, daemon model) for authoring and exporting in Figma.\n40: - [tool_surface.md](tool_surface.md) - the CLI command gating taxonomy. The MCP path here is a separate, opt-in read surface, not part of that gating.\n41: - Code Mode mechanics (naming, prefixed env, discovery): [mcp-code-mode SKILL.md](../../../mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md).\n42: \n43: Claims are tagged **[CONFIRMED]** (read from this repo's `.utcp_config.json` this session, or from the cited research digests) or **[INFERRED]** (reasoned, needs a live `tool_info()` / `list_tools()` to fix the exact string). The Framelink tool **names and input schemas are [INFERRED]** until a live discovery call confirms them, because the community server's per-tool schema is not pinned in this repo.\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 2. THE REGISTERED `figma` MANUAL\n48: \n49: The `figma` manual is already present in `.utcp_config.json` under `manual_call_templates[]`. Read it before changing anything. **[CONFIRMED: read from `.utcp_config.json` this session]**\n50: \n51: ```json\n52: {\n53:   \"name\": \"figma\",\n54:   \"call_template_type\": \"mcp\",\n55:   \"config\": {\n56:     \"mcpServers\": {\n57:       \"figma\": {\n58:         \"transport\": \"stdio\",\n59:         \"command\": \"npx\",\n60:         \"args\": [\"-y\", \"figma-developer-mcp@latest\", \"--stdio\"],\n61:         \"env\": { \"FIGMA_API_KEY\": \"${FIGMA_API_KEY}\" }\n62:       }\n63:     }\n64:   }\n65: }\n66: ```\n67: \n68: What it provides: the Framelink `figma-developer-mcp` server (npm `figma-developer-mcp`, v0.12.0 confirmed published) wraps the Figma REST API and **simplifies Figma file data for coding agents**, i.e. design context an agent can turn into code. **[CONFIRMED: research digest, npm view]** It is a **third-party** server, not Figma's official MCP. **[CONFIRMED]**\n69: \n70: Transport is **stdio** over `npx`, which matches every other manual registered here (`chrome_devtools_1/2`, `clickup_official`, `github` are all stdio). No HTTP manual exists in this repo, so the stdio Framelink path is the proven one. **[CONFIRMED: `.utcp_config.json` inspection]**\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 3. THE `.env` TOKEN (prefixed)\n75: \n76: The manual's config references `${FIGMA_API_KEY}`, but **Code Mode prefixes every environment variable with the manual name**. So the `.env` entry must be the **prefixed** form, not the bare name. **[CONFIRMED: mcp-code-mode SKILL.md §4 \"Critical: Prefixed Environment Variables\"]**\n77: \n78: ```bash\n79: # .env (project root)\n80: figma_FIGMA_API_KEY=figd_your_token_here\n81: ```\n82: \n83: - The token is a **Figma personal access token** (begins `figd_`). Generate it in Figma → Settings → Security → personal access tokens. **[INFERRED: standard Figma token shape, verify in Figma]**\n84: - Using bare `FIGMA_API_KEY=...` will fail with `Error: Variable 'figma_FIGMA_API_KEY' not found`. **[CONFIRMED: mcp-code-mode SKILL.md §4]**\n85: - This is the **only** setup the MCP path needs, since the manual is already registered (Section 2). Never paste the token into user-facing output, and treat it as a credential.\n86: \n87: | Manual name | Config reference   | `.env` variable        |\n88: | ----------- | ------------------ | ---------------------- |\n89: | `figma`     | `${FIGMA_API_KEY}` | `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`  |\n90: \n\n(Showing lines 1-90 of 170. Use offset=91 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Figma MCP Wiring (optional, via Code Mode)\"\ndescription: \"Wiring the OPTIONAL Figma MCP into this project's Code Mode: the already-registered Framelink figma manual, the prefixed .env token, the discover-first flow, and a runnable call_tool_chain example. The CLI works fully alone; the MCP is opt-in.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma mcp\"\n  - \"figma mcp code mode\"\n  - \"figma-developer-mcp\"\n  - \"pull figma design context\"\n  - \"figma get_design_context\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\nversion: 1.0.0.3\n---\n\n# Figma MCP Wiring (optional, via Code Mode)\n\n> **IMPORTANT:** This skill works **fully with the `figma-ds-cli` alone**, and the MCP is **opt-in**. Before invoking any Figma MCP tool, always **discover first** (`search_tools` / `tool_info`) and confirm the `figma` manual and its exact tool names are present. Never guess a tool name, and never claim the MCP works until discovery confirms it.\n\n---\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Figma MCP Wiring (optional, via Code Mode)\"\ndescription: \"Wiring the OPTIONAL Figma MCP into this project's Code Mode: the already-registered Framelink figma manual, the prefixed .env token, the discover-first flow, and a runnable call_tool_chain example. The CLI works fully alone; the MCP is opt-in.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma mcp\"\n  - \"figma mcp code mode\"\n  - \"figma-developer-mcp\"\n  - \"pull figma design context\"\n  - \"figma get_design_context\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\nversion: 1.0.0.3\n---\n\n# Figma MCP Wiring (optional, via Code Mode)\n\n> **IMPORTANT:** This skill works **fully with the `figma-ds-cli` alone**, and the MCP is **opt-in**. Before invoking any Figma MCP tool, always **discover first** (`search_tools` / `tool_info`) and confirm the `figma` manual and its exact tool names are present. Never guess a tool name, and never claim the MCP works until discovery confirms it.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Core Principle\n\nWiring here means the agent reaches Figma's **read** surface (design context, variables, metadata) through this project's **Code Mode** transport. The Code Mode manual named `figma` is **already registered** in `.utcp_config.json` (community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp`, stdio, `npx`), so nothing new needs to be installed for the MCP path. The only setup step is a `.env` entry with a Figma personal access token.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Pull Figma file/node data into the agent so it can generate or reconcile code against a design.\n- The work is codegen-from-design, not authoring or exporting from the live Desktop session.\n\nThe CLI vs MCP routing line:\n\n- **`figma-ds-cli` (CLI) = author/modify/export IN Figma.** It drives the live Figma Desktop session to create/render/modify nodes, manage tokens and variables, and export assets/JSX/CSS/screenshots. This is the primary surface.\n- **Figma MCP (Code Mode) = pull design data INTO the agent for codegen.** Use it only when the agent needs Figma design context as model input (file/node data, variables, screenshots) to generate or align code. The MCP does not drive Figma Desktop.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n- [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - the primary CLI surface (binary identity, connect modes, daemon model) for authoring and exporting in Figma.\n- [tool_surface.md](tool_surface.md) - the CLI command gating taxonomy. The MCP path here is a separate, opt-in read surface, not part of that gating.\n- Code Mode mechanics (naming, prefixed env, discovery): [mcp-code-mode SKILL.md](../../../mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md).\n\nClaims are tagged **[CONFIRMED]** (read from this repo's `.utcp_config.json` this session, or from the cited research digests) or **[INFERRED]** (reasoned, needs a live `tool_info()` / `list_tools()` to fix the exact string). The Framelink tool **names and input schemas are [INFERRED]** until a live discovery call confirms them, because the community server's per-tool schema is not pinned in this repo.\n\n---\n\n## 2. THE REGISTERED `figma` MANUAL\n\nThe `figma` manual is already present in `.utcp_config.json` under `manual_call_templates[]`. Read it before changing anything. **[CONFIRMED: read from `.utcp_config.json` this session]**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"figma\",\n  \"call_template_type\": \"mcp\",\n  \"config\": {\n    \"mcpServers\": {\n      \"figma\": {\n        \"transport\": \"stdio\",\n        \"command\": \"npx\",\n        \"args\": [\"-y\", \"figma-developer-mcp@latest\", \"--stdio\"],\n        \"env\": { \"FIGMA_API_KEY\": \"${FIGMA_API_KEY}\" }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nWhat it provides: the Framelink `figma-developer-mcp` server (npm `figma-developer-mcp`, v0.12.0 confirmed published) wraps the Figma REST API and **simplifies Figma file data for coding agents**, i.e. design context an agent can turn into code. **[CONFIRMED: research digest, npm view]** It is a **third-party** server, not Figma's official MCP. **[CONFIRMED]**\n\nTransport is **stdio** over `npx`, which matches every other manual registered here (`chrome_devtools_1/2`, `clickup_official`, `github` are all stdio). No HTTP manual exists in this repo, so the stdio Framelink path is the proven one. **[CONFIRMED: `.utcp_config.json` inspection]**\n\n---\n\n## 3. THE `.env` TOKEN (prefixed)\n\nThe manual's config references `${FIGMA_API_KEY}`, but **Code Mode prefixes every environment variable with the manual name**. So the `.env` entry must be the **prefixed** form, not the bare name. **[CONFIRMED: mcp-code-mode SKILL.md §4 \"Critical: Prefixed Environment Variables\"]**\n\n```bash\n# .env (project root)\nfigma_FIGMA_API_KEY=figd_your_token_here\n```\n\n- The token is a **Figma personal access token** (begins `figd_`). Generate it in Figma → Settings → Security → personal access tokens. **[INFERRED: standard Figma token shape, verify in Figma]**\n- Using bare `FIGMA_API_KEY=...` will fail with `Error: Variable 'figma_FIGMA_API_KEY' not found`. **[CONFIRMED: mcp-code-mode SKILL.md §4]**\n- This is the **only** setup the MCP path needs, since the manual is already registered (Section 2). Never paste the token into user-facing output, and treat it as a credential.\n\n| Manual name | Config reference   | `.env` variable        |\n| ----------- | ------------------ | ---------------------- |\n| `figma`     | `${FIGMA_API_KEY}` | `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`  |\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":90,"totalLines":170,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md","time":{"start":1784198815980,"end":1784198815986}},"id":"prt_f6a8960ea001EZ6OvK16DpWxA8","sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","messageID":"msg_f6a893a13001pGh9bOzrVJX2sZ"}}
