{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784199020114,"sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_0c131174b8314139b506bf9d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"{\n  \"lineage\": \"glm\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-glm-1784198125985-iw9229\",\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research\",\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    { \"id\": \"q3\", \"text\": \"What rate limits apply, and do they differ between free and paid tiers?\", \"status\": \"open\", \"note\": \"CONFIRMED UNDOCUMENTED in all authoritative sources (skill repo + refero.design SPA). Unverified gap — resolve via live probe in a later phase.\", \"resolvedAs\": \"negative_knowledge\" },\n    { \"id\": \"q4\", \"text\": \"What is the free vs paid gating — which tools/capabilities/result volumes are free vs paid-only?\", \"status\": \"open\", \"note\": \"Only signal: craft knowledge = no account; live MCP = auth required. Exact tier boundaries UNDOCUMENTED. Unverified gap.\", \"resolvedAs\": \"negative_knowledge\" }\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    { \"id\": \"q1\", \"text\": \"What tools does the Refero MCP server expose (names, parameters, response shapes) for UI-design-reference search across apps, screens, flows, elements?\", \"status\": \"resolved\", \"resolvedInIteration\": 1, \"evidence\": \"iteration-001.md F1\" },\n    { \"id\": \"q2\", \"text\": \"What auth model does the Refero MCP expect through mcp-remote (anonymous, OAuth, API key)?\", \"status\": \"resolved\", \"resolvedInIteration\": 2, \"evidence\": \"iteration-002.md F8\", \"answer\": \"Two paths: mcp-remote OAuth browser flow (existing manual, empty env, interactive first-use) OR Bearer token via HTTP header; endpoint https://api.refero.design/mcp\" },\n    { \"id\": \"q5\", \"text\": \"What conventions does the refero_skill repo document that the mcp-refero transport packet should mirror?\", \"status\": \"resolved\", \"resolvedInIteration\": 1, \"evidence\": \"iteration-001.md F5\" },\n    { \"id\": \"q6\", \"text\": \"How should a read-only Code-Mode-only transport packet be authored atop the existing mcp-remote manual, paired with sk-design judgment?\", \"status\": \"resolved\", \"resolvedInIteration\": 2, \"evidence\": \"iteration-002.md F9, F10\", \"answer\": \"Simpler read-only-only peer of mcp-figma (MCP-only, no CLI); SKILL.md + references(refero_mcp_tools, tool_surface collapsed to read-only, mcp_wiring, troubleshooting) + assets(utcp_refero_manual, env_template); Code Mode naming refero.refero_<tool>; pairs with sk-design for judgment\" }\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    { \"id\": \"f1\", \"iteration\": 1, \"text\": \"8 read-only tools across 3 layers: styles (search_styles, get_style), screens (search_screens, get_screen, get_similar_screens, get_screen_image), flows (search_flows, get_flow)\", \"source\": \"references/mcp-tools.md\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f2\", \"iteration\": 1, \"text\": \"Documented client mistakes: no old _tool names, no get_design_guidance, no image_size/include_similar on get_screen, no limit/image_size/include_similar on search tools, response_format only where schema shows it\", \"source\": \"references/mcp-tools.md\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f3\", \"iteration\": 1, \"text\": \"Auth: Bearer-token HTTP transport OR mcp-remote OAuth browser flow; endpoint https://api.refero.design/mcp; existing manual uses mcp-remote with empty env\", \"source\": \"README + .utcp_config.json\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f4\", \"iteration\": 1, \"text\": \"Coverage limit: styles are web-marketing-scoped only (no dashboards/auth/settings/iOS as style systems); screens+flows support platform web|ios\", \"source\": \"references/mcp-tools.md + SKILL.md\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f5\", \"iteration\": 1, \"text\": \"refero_skill is a standalone design-methodology skill (peer of sk-design), NOT an mcp-tooling transport; MIT; SKILL.md + references/ + assets/\", \"source\": \"README + SKILL.md\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f6\", \"iteration\": 1, \"text\": \"Existing .utcp_config.json manual is a minimal stdio-over-mcp-remote bridge, empty env; transport packet authored atop it read-only\", \"source\": \".utcp_config.json\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f7\", \"iteration\": 2, \"text\": \"NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE: free-vs-paid gating and rate limits are NOT publicly documented — refero.design root/mcp/pricing are all SPAs (title only); skill repo documents neither. Only signal: craft knowledge no account, live MCP requires auth.\", \"source\": \"iteration-002.md F7; WebFetch on refero.design{,/mcp,/pricing}\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f8\", \"iteration\": 2, \"text\": \"Auth lifecycle: path A mcp-remote OAuth (interactive browser sign-in first-use, token cached, empty env); path B Bearer token (HTTP header; token-grant flow undocumented). Code Mode env-prefix rule: refero_<NAME> if token wired via env. First-use browser sign-in is an operational constraint (headless/CI needs path B).\", \"source\": \"iteration-002.md F8; mcp-figma mcp_wiring.md §3\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f9\", \"iteration\": 2, \"text\": \"Transport-packet layout: mcp-refero is a SIMPLER read-only-only peer of mcp-figma (MCP-only, no CLI, no gating taxonomy). Files: SKILL.md + references/{refero_mcp_tools, tool_surface(read-only-only), mcp_wiring, troubleshooting} + assets/{utcp_refero_manual, env_template}. Code Mode calling: refero.refero_<tool>.\", \"source\": \"iteration-002.md F9; mcp-figma references\" },\n    { \"id\": \"f10\", \"iteration\": 2, \"text\": \"Layer-discipline routing rule (transport must surface): styles first (visual direction) -> screens (concrete UI) -> flows (journeys); combine layers; styles web-marketing-scoped caveat. Judgment routed to sk-design; transport never duplicates refero_skill methodology.\", \"source\": \"iteration-002.md F10; SKILL.md Tool Routing\" }\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    { \"approach\": \"Scrape the JS-rendered body of refero.design/mcp for structured pricing/gating data\", \"reason\": \"SPA returns only a title via WebFetch; no crawlable body\", \"evidence\": \"iteration-001.md\", \"iteration\": 1 },\n    { \"approach\": \"Further scraping of refero.design/* SPA routes (root, pricing) for pricing/gating\", \"reason\": \"All routes yield only the title; pricing/gating facts are not web-crawlable\", \"evidence\": \"iteration-002.md F7\", \"iteration\": 2 }\n  ],\n  \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n  \"rejectedPatternIndex\": [],\n  \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n  \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": []\n}\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/findings-registry.json"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/findings-registry.json","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/009-mcp-refero/001-research/research/lineages/glm/findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1784199020108,"end":1784199020113}},"id":"prt_f6a8c7e42001O0s9jOMbZxLoGb","sessionID":"ses_095812142ffehVMtk1LE9C34ba","messageID":"msg_f6a8be8f9001V7GANlLzr24QKx"}}
